The paper deals with the problem of sparse signal decomposition, which is a common topic in several sub-fields of computer science. However, the focus on stability against noise and the use of specific algorithms for sparse decomposition suggest that the paper is most likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of mathematical optimization techniques and the analysis of the uniqueness of sparse decompositions suggest that the paper could also belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) or Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
